claim.claim-text:
17. An x-ray analysis system comprising:
an x-ray engine having an x-ray excitation path for producing an x-ray excitation beam, the x-ray excitation beam directed toward an x-ray analysis focal area;
a sample chamber for presenting a sample to the x-ray analysis focal area, the x-ray analysis focal area disposed within space defined by the chamber;
an x-ray detection path for collecting secondary x-rays from the focal area and directing the secondary x-rays toward a detector;
a first x-ray transparent barrier on a wall of the chamber through which the x-ray excitation beam and the secondary x-rays pass; and
a support structure in the space defined by the chamber, for guiding the sample stream through the focal area and spaced from the barrier, the barrier being thereby separated from the sample stream such that the sample does not continuously contact the barrier.
